  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extensions, by virtue of their inappropriate form, design and prominent location would create an incongruous and dominant feature that would be harmful to the appearance of the locally listed buildings, the integrity of the unimpaired and uniform terrace and the character and appearance of the Duncan Terrace/Colebrook Row Conservation Area . This would be contrary to policies D4, D11, D22 and D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002), policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011, policies 7.4 and 7.8 of the London Plan 2011, emerging policies DM1 and DM3 of the Development Management Policies 2012 and guidance contained within the Duncan Terrace/Colebrook Row Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006)."
